(20, 1, '2014-07-13 18:25:54', '2014-07-13 18:25:54', '<p style="color: #292929;">The Naive Creative welcomes submissions in the realm of visual art, photography, sculpture, painting, installation, collage, paper, illustration or drawing, street art, architecture, industrial design, textile, animation, documentaries, and anything else involving a strong (generally non-digital) visual aspect. In the course of daily coverage we generally do not cover fashion, book or app reviews, coverage of websites, music, literature, phone accessories, call for entries, or upcoming events without supporting imagery.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>How to Submit to The Naive Creative</h2>\r\n<p style="color: #292929;">If you wish to send tips regarding work that is not your own, please do. Just use the email address provided below.</p>\r\n<p style="color: #292929;">Here’s the skinny on sending your own work: many submissions arrive each week so <em>please</em> help me understand your project quickly. Send a <em><strong>brief</strong></em> email with a basic description of your work and please attach a few relevant images sized at 800px wide or much larger. File size is not an issue. <strong>Zip files, DOCs, press releases, RARs, and PDFs will not be reviewed</strong>. In some cases you may include one or two web links directly to the project in question (ie. your film or your website). If what you wish to show is buried in a portfolio or gallery website we may not click through everything, so help me get started in the right spot.</p>\r\n<p style="color: #292929;">You will receive an automatic response if your submission is successfully received, so there is no need to resubmit your project after that. Every submission is carefully considered, though due to volume we are unable to respond personally. Submissions can be sent to <a href="mailto:submissions@thenaivecreative.com">submissions@thenaivecreative.com</a></p>\r\n<strong>Attention galleries and event organizers:</strong> we appreciate the submission of your next exhibition/event. As this is a visual blog, please attach relevant installation views or existing photos of the artist’s work. If no imagery exists please submit when you’re able to obtain photos. Thank you.', 'Submit', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'submit', '', '', '2014-07-15 16:07:15', '2014-07-15 16:07:15', '', 0, 'http://localhost:8888/TheNaiveCreative/?page_id=20', 0, 'page', '', 0),
