(162, 1, '2014-10-14 04:26:16', '2014-10-14 04:26:16', '<a href="http://localhost:8888/TheNaiveCreative/wp-content/uploads/2014/10/0022.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-large wp-image-176" src="http://localhost:8888/TheNaiveCreative/wp-content/uploads/2014/10/0022-1024x548.jpg" alt="002" width="970" height="519" /></a>\r\n\r\nRead on below to hear about Lauren’s journey thus far and view a sneak peek of her project. Additionally, be sure to visit <a href="http://laurenmarek.vsco.co/grid/1">Lauren’s VSCO Grid™</a> for more images of life in Bellville and for insights she’s shared on her <a href="http://laurenmarek.vsco.co/journal/first-home-game">VSCO Journal</a>.When it comes to getting the shots that capture the height of the action, Lauren has had to push herself as a photographer. “The most challenging aspect of this project so far has definitely been finding the balance of blending into the sidelines and getting up close and personal to the players. My personality and style of photography is generally non-intrusive, so shooting in the middle of all this action and getting really close to the players has taken me out of my comfort zone.” The season has taught Lauren a lot in the way of timing and autonomy with her subjects. “As every game passes, I''m learning the flow and testing my limits, always making sure to never distract the players from what they are trying to accomplish on the field.”\r\n\r\n<a href="http://localhost:8888/TheNaiveCreative/wp-content/uploads/2014/10/0032.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-large wp-image-177" src="http://localhost:8888/TheNaiveCreative/wp-content/uploads/2014/10/0032-1024x495.jpg" alt="003" width="970" height="468" /></a>\r\n\r\nRead on below to hear about Lauren’s journey thus far and view a sneak peek of her project. Additionally, be sure to visit Lauren’s VSCO Grid™ for more images of life in Bellville and for insights she’s shared on her VSCO Journal.When it comes to getting the shots that capture the height of the act